 The area under the curve $y = \sqrt{x-1}$ between $x=1$ and $x=5$ is as shown below
%
\begin{align}

\includegraphics[scale=1.4]{wrong.svg}
\end{align}
%text
%

reason.tex:
%text
 $y = \sqrt{x-1} \implies y^2 = x - 1$. This looks like a parabola 
 Bit notice also that $ y =0$ when $x = 1$. Hence, if anything, the parabola should look like this
%
\begin{align}

\includegraphics[scale=1.4]{right.svg}
\end{align}
%text
 And the required area is the shaded bit%
